<TEXT>
Romania's two largest unions said some 2m workers participated in
yesterday's general strike, in the biggest union action since the overthrow
of communist rule in 1989, writes Virginia Marsh in Bucharest. The strike,
in protest at the lack of economic reform, hit hardest in the chemical,
petrochemical, metal, transport and food industries, the unions said.
Harbour workers closed the Danube port of Galati and also disrupted shipping
at Constanta, the main Black Sea port, Radio Bucharest reported. Health and
education were also seriously affected but roads and telecommunications
werre unaffected.
