FT  01 MAR 94 / Treuhand finalises sale of Laubag, Veag
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JUDY DEMPSEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The German Treuhand privatisation agency yesterday sealed the sale of
eastern Germany's brown coal fields and the region's largest electricity
company, writes Judy Dempsey. The sale of the Laubag lignite mines and Veag
ends a two-year attempt by the agency to sell the two companies. Laubag was
sold to a consortium, led by Rheinbraun, a subsidiary of RWE, and which
includes PreussenElektra and Bayernwerk. The consortium is expected to
invest DM6bn (Pounds 2.3bn) in the fields and to guarantee at least 10,000
jobs.
