FT  01 MAR 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Tea Broker's Association reports, landed very strong demand. Bright East
Africans sold well and often appreciated several pence. Coloury medium teas
met keen competition and prices advanced 5 to 15p and sometimes more.
Plainer descriptions were firm to dearer. Brighter ceylons gained up to 15p,
others moved 2 to 4p higher. Offshore strong demand. Brighter teas were 4 to
8p dearer while plainer types remained fully firm. Quality 195p/kg nom, good
medium 145p/kg, medium 125p/kg, low medium 86p/kg. The highest price
realised this week was 215p for a Rwanda pf. 1.
