<HEADLINE>
FT  28 FEB 94 / International Company News: Asahi Glass suffers sharp fall
in profit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMIKO TERAZONO
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Asahi Glass, Japan's largest glass maker, suffered a sharp fall in earnings
as the economic downturn hit demand for glass, writes Emiko Terazono in
Tokyo.
It reported a 34.4 per cent fall in parent company pre-tax profits for the
year to December to Y26.2bn (Dollars 250m), on a 4.7 per cent decline in
sales to Y964.5bn. After-tax profits fell 24.7 per cent to Y15.4bn.
Sales of glass and construction materials decreased 8.3 per cent to
Y479.4bn. due to sluggish demand for high-performance glass from the
construction industry and fabricated glass from the automobile industry.
On a consolidated basis, Asahi reported a 55 per cent fall in pre-tax
profits to Y20.1bn on a 6.8 per cent decline in sales to Y1,227.3bn.
For the current year Asahi expects the glass market to recover and sees
parent pre-tax profits rising 6.6 per cent to Y28bn on a 0.6 per cent sales
increase to Y970bn.
</TEXT>
