<HEADLINE>
FT  28 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Piper European trust to be launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A new European smaller companies investment trust aims to raise up to Pounds
50m through a placing and offer for subscription.
Piper European Smaller Companies is being launched by Piper International
Asset Management, the Edinburgh-based fund management subsidiary of the US
Piper Jaffray group.
The trust will invest in European companies, not including the UK, with
market capitalisations of up to Pounds 250m, with the aim of achieving
long-term capital growth.
The trust will be managed to qualify for investment via a personal equity
plan.
Managers of the fund say they believe the time is right to launch a European
smaller companies fund because of rising economic growth in Europe, and the
tendency of smaller companies to outperform larger companies at times of
economic growth.
As yet, there are relatively few investment trusts specialising in this
area.
The team of managers were all formerly with N Dunn &amp; Co, a small fund
management company which was recently acquired by Piper.
Ordinary shares in the trust will be offered at 100p, with one warrant
attached to every five shares.
</TEXT>
