others. The Portuguese escudo ended the week barely stronger than the
peseta. Currencies, Page 37
The chart shows the member currencies of the exchange rate mechanism
measured against the weakest currency in the system. Most of the currencies
can fluctuate within 15 per cent of agreed central rates against the other
members of the mechanism. The exceptions are the D-Mark and the guilder
which move in a narrow 2.25 per cent band.
